{"parentUuid":"56f637f0-a8a0-4226-926e-275c4e084774","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a694ec9ee8d30ccac","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CY4RRwWTfCu36nnDejwihZ","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AlphaEvolve limitation problems with automated evaluator score constraint excludes manual experimentation\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: LLM-Driven Code Evolution\",\"url\":\"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/alphaevolve-framework\"},{\"title\":\"Google’s AlphaEvolve: The AI agent that reclaimed 0.7% of Google’s compute – and how to copy it | VentureBeat\",\"url\":\"https://venturebeat.com/ai/googles-alphaevolve-the-ai-agent-that-reclaimed-0-7-of-googles-compute-and-how-to-copy-it\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve | cbarkinozer | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://cbarkinozer.medium.com/alphaevolve-419242a0a4b4\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery\",\"url\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/DeepMind.com/Blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/AlphaEvolve.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Google’s AlphaEvolve and the Future of Automated Discovery | by Devansh | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://machine-learning-made-simple.medium.com/googles-alphaevolve-and-the-future-of-automated-discovery-6eb8033879dd\"},{\"title\":\"Can AlphaEvolve Change How We Solve Problems? A Look Inside DeepMind’s Latest Breakthrough\",\"url\":\"https://www.aiwire.net/2025/05/27/can-alphaevolve-change-how-we-solve-problems-a-look-inside-deepminds-latest-breakthrough/\"},{\"title\":\"Google DeepMind AlphaEvolve (May 2026): Algorithm Discovery Moves From Lab Demo to Production System | Buildmind AI\",\"url\":\"https://buildmind.ai/blog/google-deepmind-alphaevolve-may-2026-production-algorithm-discovery/\"},{\"title\":\"Paper Review: AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery | by Andrew Lukyanenko | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://artgor.medium.com/paper-review-alphaevolve-a-coding-agent-for-scientific-and-algorithmic-discovery-5732a876c2e2\"},{\"title\":\"Evolving Local Corrections for Global Constructions in Combinatorics\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.06692\"},{\"title\":\"Evolving Ranking Functions for Canonical Blow-Ups in Positive Characteristic\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2602.06553\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found relevant information about AlphaEvolve's limitation regarding automated evaluators and manual experimentation.\n\nThe primary limitation is the need for an automated evaluator; problems requiring manual experimentation or \"wet-lab\" feedback are currently out of scope for this specific approach. This constraint is reinforced by the official AlphaEvolve paper, which states that the use of an automated evaluation metric, while offering AlphaEvolve a key advantage, is also a limitation—in particular, it puts tasks that require manual experimentation out of scope.\n\nThe primary limitation of AlphaEvolve is its reliance on problems where an automated evaluation function can be designed, making it well-suited for computational and mathematical sciences but less applicable to domains requiring physical experiments.\n\nThis fundamental constraint is considered the current critical constraint for AlphaEvolve—the need for a human-defined, machine-executable evaluation function—and is where the next major frontier likely lies.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"d930d69e-0a5e-405f-8edc-d00654ccce99","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:48.179Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"AlphaEvolve limitation problems with automated evaluator score constraint excludes manual experimentation","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01TZwkRFLE3RpVFeHVpt7D9r","content":[{"title":"AlphaEvolve: LLM-Driven Code Evolution","url":"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/alpha