eed for an automated evaluator; problems requiring manual experimentation or \"wet-lab\" feedback are currently out of scope for this specific approach. This constraint is reinforced by the official AlphaEvolve paper, which states that the use of an automated evaluation metric, while offering AlphaEvolve a key advantage, is also a limitation—in particular, it puts tasks that require manual experimentation out of scope.\n\nThe primary limitation of AlphaEvolve is its reliance on problems where an automated evaluation function can be designed, making it well-suited for computational and mathematical sciences but less applicable to domains requiring physical experiments.\n\nThis fundamental constraint is considered the current critical constraint for AlphaEvolve—the need for a human-defined, machine-executable evaluation function—and is where the next major frontier likely lies."],"durationSeconds":7.6596397919990125,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"56f637f0-a8a0-4226-926e-275c4e084774","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
