{"parentUuid":"1fc453db-5622-4da5-b15d-6ff7713815e3","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a694ec9ee8d30ccac","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0123Yg7yYFKDuEGx5yHK2Mon","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AlphaEvolve Ars Technica OR \"MIT Technology Review\" automated evaluator limitation problems with clear answer\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery\",\"url\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/DeepMind.com/Blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/AlphaEvolve.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Can AlphaEvolve Change How We Solve Problems? A Look Inside DeepMind’s Latest Breakthrough\",\"url\":\"https://www.aiwire.net/2025/05/27/can-alphaevolve-change-how-we-solve-problems-a-look-inside-deepminds-latest-breakthrough/\"},{\"title\":\"Google’s AlphaEvolve: The AI agent that reclaimed 0.7% of Google’s compute – and how to copy it | VentureBeat\",\"url\":\"https://venturebeat.com/ai/googles-alphaevolve-the-ai-agent-that-reclaimed-0-7-of-googles-compute-and-how-to-copy-it\"},{\"title\":\"Google DeepMind's AlphaEvolve: A Breakthrough in AI-Driven Scientific Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://theoutpost.ai/news-story/google-deep-mind-s-alpha-evolve-a-breakthrough-in-ai-driven-algorithm-discovery-15378/\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: How AI-Driven Algorithm Discovery Is Rewriting Computing | by Greg Robison | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://gregrobison.medium.com/alphaevolve-how-ai-driven-algorithm-discovery-is-rewriting-computing-4f27c88d8b27\"},{\"title\":\"Google DeepMind Creates Super-Advanced AI That Can Invent New Algorithms - Slashdot\",\"url\":\"https://tech.slashdot.org/story/25/05/14/2212200/google-deepmind-creates-super-advanced-ai-that-can-invent-new-algorithms\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: A Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms — Google DeepMind\",\"url\":\"https://deepmind.google/blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/\"},{\"title\":\"Alignment Verifiability in Large Language Models: Normative Indistinguishability under Behavioral Evaluation\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2602.05656\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found clear information about the automated evaluator limitations of AlphaEvolve from multiple sources including Ars Technica:\n\n## AlphaEvolve's Automated Evaluator Limitation\n\nThe use of an automated evaluation metric offers AlphaEvolve a key advantage, but it is also a limitation—in particular, it puts tasks that require manual experimentation out of scope.\n\nMore specifically, the primary limitation is the need for an automated evaluator; problems requiring manual experimentation or \"wet-lab\" feedback are currently out of scope for this specific approach.\n\nAlphaEvolve can only tackle problems that come with a built-in way to evaluate success, meaning that users must provide it with a formula or some method to automatically test its solutions.\n\nBecause problems in mathematics, computer science, and system optimization typically permit automated evaluation metrics, AlphaEvolve's efforts focus on these domains.\n\nThe article from Ars Technica (referenced in the Slashdot summary) confirms that while AlphaEvolve uses \"an automatic evaluation system\" to handle complex algorithmic problems, this same requirement fundamentally restricts its applicability to problems that can be automatically evaluated.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"299ecdf7-fc5b-43f0-9eb0-c7fdf71f06dd","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:43.002Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"AlphaEvolve Ars Technica OR \"MIT Technology Review\" automated evaluator limitation problems with clear answer","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01NG5VGtxQrzyM9Lqu9wTq3v","content":[{"title":"AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery","url":"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/DeepMind.com/Blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/AlphaEvolve.pdf"},{"title":"Can AlphaEvolve Change How We Solve Problems? A Look Inside DeepMind’s Latest Breakthrough","url":"https://www.aiwire.net/2025/05/27/can-alphaevolve-change-how-we-solve-problems-a-look-inside-deepminds-latest-breakthrough/"},{"title":"Google’s AlphaEvolve: The AI agent that reclaimed 0.7% of Google’s compute – and how to copy it | VentureBeat","url":"https://venturebeat.com/ai/googles-alphaevolve-the-ai-agent-that-reclaimed-0-7-of-googles-compute-and-how-to-copy-it"},{"title":"Google DeepMind's AlphaEvolve: A Breakthrough in AI-Driven Scientific Discovery","url":"https://theoutpost.ai/news-story/google-deep-mind-s-alpha-evolve-a-breakthrough-in-ai-driven-algorithm-discovery-15378/"},{"title":"AlphaEvolve: How AI-Driven Algorithm Discovery Is Rewriting Computing | by Greg Robison | Medium","url":"https://gregrobison.medium.com/alphaevolve-how-ai-driven-algorithm-discovery-is-rewriting-computing-4f27c88d8b27"},{"title":"Google DeepMind Creates Super-Advanced AI That Can Invent New Algorithms - Slashdot","url":"https://tech.slashdot.org/story/25/05/14/2212200/google-deepmind-creates-super-advanced-ai-that-can-invent-new-algorithms"},{"title":"AlphaEvolve: A Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms — Google DeepMind","url":"https://deepmind.google/blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/"},{"title":"Alignment Verifiability in Large Language Models: Normative Indistinguishability under Behavioral Evaluation","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2602.05656"}]},"Based on the search results, I found clear information about the automated evaluator limitations of AlphaEvolve from multiple sources including Ars Technica:\n\n## AlphaEvolve's Automated Evaluator Limitation\n\nThe use of an automated evaluation metric offers AlphaEvolve a key advantage, but it is also a limitation—in particular, it puts tasks that require manual experimentation out of scope.\n\nMore specifically, the primary limitation is the need for an automated evaluator; problems requiring manual experimentation or \"wet-lab\" feedback are currently out of scope for this specific approach.\n\nAlphaEvolve can only tackle problems that come with a built-in way to evaluate success, meaning that users must provide it with a formula or some method to automatically test its solutions.\n\nBecause problems in mathematics, computer science, and system optimization typically permit automated evaluation metrics, AlphaEvolve's efforts focus on these domains.\n\nThe article from Ars Technica (referenced in the Slashdot summary) confirms that while AlphaEvolve uses \"an automatic evaluation system\" to handle complex algorithmic problems, this same requirement fundamentally restricts its applicability to problems that can be automatically evaluated."],"durationSeconds":6.9250136660002175,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"1fc453db-5622-4da5-b15d-6ff7713815e3","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
